HEADWORD: Papyrine
<hw>Pap"y*rine</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>papyrin</ets> made of paper. See <er>Paper</er>.]</ety>
<def>Imitation parchment, made by soaking unsized paper in dilute
sulphuric acid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

